  <h2>Join San Telmo's Kitchen Team</h2>
  <p>Our specialty imported 2.5 meter charcoal grill, known in Argentina as a Parrilla, is barbeque paradise and people are coming from all around to see the magic happening over the hot coals.</p>
  <p>You will learn to display your skills in our open kitchen with close guidance and mentoring of Mike Patrick (Head Chef) and Chris Moran (Sous Chef). Using top local produce and the latest kitchen equipment you will learn about South American cuisine and culture.</p>
  <p>Through the experience in an open kitchen and the direct contact you will have with customers you will form a fundamental part of the lively culture and atmosphere of the restaurant, improving your people skills and the vibe of the kitchen. We definitely appreciate the importance of a balanced work/life so we provide flexible working hours that can be tailored to meet family and social needs. For the right applicant we are offering extensive management training in a positive work environment, with opportunity for carreer progression.</p>
  <p>The applicant we are looking for will be motivated and passionate about food and their career in restaurants with a positive “can do” attiude. They must be punctual, hardworking and committed to learn and develop with San Telmo.</p>
  <p>Genuine interest should be directed with a CV and expression of interest to <%= mail_to "info@santelmo.com.au" %></p>
  <h2>Join our Floor and Bar Team</h2>
  <p>We are allways open to applications from commited and motivated Floor and Bar staff who are interested in learning and growing with the San Telmo team.</p>
  <p>We have the only exclusively Argentinian wine list in the Australia provide ongoing training in the wine (knowledge about the Argentine wine regions and styles from specialist winemakers in the region) as well as the comida and culture.</p>
  <p>You will be working with an exclusive and top quality product from our self imported wines to South American cocktails, 5 senses coffee and the fresh produce and asado that comes from our amazing kitchen team and unique Parrilla.</p>
  <p>We offer a fun and lively work environment with flexible hours and attainable rewards, with in house and exterior management training for the right people. Our aim is to help develop staffs skills to maximise their potential and grow within the business.</p>
  <p>The right candidates will be committed, have exceptional customer (AND kitchen) interaction skills and be ready to embrace the culture of San Telmo and the Argentine ethos:</p>
  <p><em>“Eating, drinking and most importantly living are there to be enjoyed with friends and family”</em></p>
  <p>If this is you then send your CV and an expression of interest to <%= mail_to "info@santelmo.com.au" %></p>
